	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I was programming an Apple IIe in assembly language back in middle school in the early 1990s, which is how I learned 6502 asm. I became interested in NES emulation sometime in the 2000s, and I wrote a few demos that worked on the emulators of the time but not necessarily on NES hardware because I had no way to test. Zophar.net had some of the documents (including koitsu's that you mention). I coded for the NES off and on, mixed with PC and GBA coding. My interest in NES programming really picked up once I got my PowerPak and could see my work run on the real thing.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
