	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />In general, NES ROM expansion requires <ol style="list-style-type: decimal"><li>decomposition into header, PRG, and CHR (whether through iNES splitter or an unzip program), </li><li>duplication of any fixed last bank of PRG ROM, </li><li>normalization of bank numbers written to the mapper (this might be what was considered "impossible" in the general case), and </li><li>recombining header, PRG, and CHR. </li></ol>
<br />I should know; I've <a href="http://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Forbidden_Four" class="postlink">expanded The Legend of Zelda</a>. I have a cousin who's been expanding SMB1 with CNROM to animate certain tiles, though I told him it was wasteful and he should try a CHR RAM based method that pushes those few tiles that animate (? and coin) during otherwise idle periods.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
